00:18:48,720 --> 00:18:51,360
 until I started preparing for this sermon.

393
00:18:51,360 --> 00:18:55,520
 And that's because they are actually stunt doubles.

394
00:18:55,520 --> 00:18:56,360
 Yeah.

395
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:01,560
 So a stunt double is a trained professional

396
00:19:01,560 --> 00:19:04,920
 who stands in for an actor to perform dangerous

397
00:19:04,920 --> 00:19:07,000
 or demanding tasks.

398
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:11,160
 So, obviously, you won't see the actual Daniel Craig

399
00:19:11,160 --> 00:19:16,720
 jumping out of a helicopter or a building.

400
00:19:16,720 --> 00:19:18,840
 It will be a stunt double.

401
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:21,080
 The two guys from the previous slides

402
00:19:21,080 --> 00:19:23,280
 were their stunt doubles.

403
00:19:23,280 --> 00:19:25,200
 So those are the people that will be doing

404
00:19:25,200 --> 00:19:26,840
 all the dangerous things.

405
00:19:26,840 --> 00:19:30,960
 Yeah, so the actor does the majority of the film

406
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:33,560
 with no regard for the stunt double.

407
00:19:33,560 --> 00:19:36,960
 All of the easy things, goes about his business.

408
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:39,800
 But when he or she comes to that scene

409
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:42,200
 that requires a bit more strength,

410
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:45,640
 that's a bit dangerous, could cause a bit of harm or pain,

411
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:48,680
 they just step aside, let the stunt double come and do it,

412
00:19:48,680 --> 00:19:51,680
 and they do it to perfection.

413
00:19:51,680 --> 00:19:54,280
 But they're always in the background.

