00:19:54,280 --> 00:19:56,520
 No one ever knows there was a stunt double.

415
00:19:56,520 --> 00:20:00,000
 It happens so quickly, and there's never a pause

416
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,240
 in the film that says,

417
00:20:02,240 --> 00:20:04,200
 "This stunt was performed by a stunt double."

418
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:06,440
 Never, ever happens.

419
00:20:06,440 --> 00:20:08,040
 And if you don't know much about films,

420
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:10,320
 or you blink a bit too quickly,

421
00:20:10,320 --> 00:20:13,880
 you may assume that it was the main actor who did it.

422
00:20:13,880 --> 00:20:16,560
 And all of the awards, all of the accolades,

423
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:18,680
 go to the main actor.

424
00:20:18,680 --> 00:20:22,200
 There is not an Oscar for stunt doubles.

425
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:23,400
 Surprise, surprise.

426
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:24,440
 - There should be, right?

427
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:26,400
 - There should be, right?

428
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:27,240
 But there isn't.

429
00:20:27,240 --> 00:20:29,440
 (laughing)

430
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:32,680
 Now, think about your own life for a second.

431
00:20:32,680 --> 00:20:36,320
 How many times have we been the main characters

432
00:20:36,320 --> 00:20:37,880
 in our own stories,

433
00:20:37,880 --> 00:20:41,840
 and relegated God to our stunt double?

434
00:20:41,840 --> 00:20:44,120
 We call him when times are tough.

435
00:20:44,120 --> 00:20:46,320
 He comes in, he does the job,

436
00:20:46,320 --> 00:20:48,280
 and then we push him to the background.

437
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:51,880
 No praise, no honor, no recognition.

438
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:54,600
 It's all about us.

439
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:57,440
 And as I was preparing for this sermon,

440
00:20:57,440 --> 00:21:00,720
 I actually had to humble myself and repent,

441
00:21:00,720 --> 00:21:04,760
 because I realized that I was doing the exact same thing.

442
00:21:04,760 --> 00:21:08,000
 I was in two minds about doing this sermon.

443
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:10,280
 And I had like a million questions.

444
00:21:10,280 --> 00:21:11,480
 I've narrowed them down.

445
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:14,080
 Should I?

446
00:21:14,080 --> 00:21:15,800
 Shouldn't I?

447
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:17,560
 All eyes on me.

448
00:21:17,560 --> 00:21:19,800
 I may not be able to just fade into the background

449
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:21,400
 after doing this.

450
00:21:21,400 --> 00:21:24,560
 I don't particularly like speaking in public.

451
00:21:24,560 --> 00:21:26,280
 What if I say the wrong thing?

452
00:21:26,280 --> 00:21:27,240
 I'm not a pastor.

453
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:29,720
 Should I be preaching?

454
00:21:29,720 --> 00:21:34,120
 Now, let's look at those questions again.

455
00:21:34,120 --> 00:21:38,880
 And I've made all of the I's and all of the me's bold.

456
00:21:38,880 --> 00:21:40,440
 So we can all count it together.

457
00:21:40,440 --> 00:21:45,440
 One, two, three, four, five, six, seven, eight.

458
00:21:45,440 --> 00:21:46,360
 Eight times.

459
00:21:46,360 --> 00:21:47,720
 And trust me, I had way more questions.

460
00:21:47,720 --> 00:21:49,800
 There's way more I's and me's.

461
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:50,640
 Loads more.

462
00:21:52,040 --> 00:21:55,200
 So how many times did I talk about myself?

463
00:21:55,200 --> 00:21:56,040
 - Eight times.

464
00:21:56,040 --> 00:21:59,080
 - How many times did I mention God?

465
00:21:59,080 --> 00:22:03,280
 How many times did I mention His will?

466
00:22:03,280 --> 00:22:05,400
 What He has to say?

467
00:22:05,400 --> 00:22:10,400
 I had made preaching and declaring His word all about me.

468
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:17,240
 And we often go about life in this exact same way.

469
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:18,520
 We live for ourselves.

470
00:22:18,520 --> 00:22:21,440
 We wake up in the morning, it's about our kids,

471
00:22:21,440 --> 00:22:25,040
 our spouses, our jobs, what we're gonna eat,

472
00:22:25,040 --> 00:22:28,360
 what we're gonna wear, what will people think of us,

473
00:22:28,360 --> 00:22:31,440
 where we need to be, what we need to do.

474
00:22:31,440 --> 00:22:36,440
 We often don't even consider what God has for us each day.

475
00:22:36,440 --> 00:22:39,680
 And we go through the motions, doing life,

476
00:22:39,680 --> 00:22:42,320
 going through the script, saying our lines,

477
00:22:42,320 --> 00:22:44,400
 until we get to the crossroad

478
00:22:44,400 --> 00:22:47,120
 where we need our trusted stunt double.

479
00:22:47,120 --> 00:22:50,520
 And in preparing for this sermon,

480
00:22:50,520 --> 00:22:54,800
 perhaps my mindset should have been this instead.

481
00:22:54,800 --> 00:23:01,000
 What does God want to share with His church?

482
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:04,120
 How will He use me?

483
00:23:04,120 --> 00:23:08,720
 I'm gonna read that again.

484
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:13,320
 What does God want to share with His church?

485
00:23:13,320 --> 00:23:18,120
 How will God, how will He use me?

486
00:23:19,120 --> 00:23:23,880
 See, once you change your perspective

487
00:23:23,880 --> 00:23:26,520
 and you shift your gaze to Him,

488
00:23:26,520 --> 00:23:31,000
 you realize that it isn't about you.

489
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:36,560
 You are not the main character.

490
00:23:36,560 --> 00:23:38,240
 He is.

491
00:23:38,240 --> 00:23:43,240
 And it is about what He wants to do in and through you.

492
00:23:43,240 --> 00:23:47,240
 Now, Zachariah had the right idea.

493
00:23:47,240 --> 00:23:49,760
 He made God the center

494
00:23:49,760 --> 00:23:53,720
 and had set his eyes on the things above.

495
00:23:53,720 --> 00:23:57,160
 Luke 1:6 says, "He and Elizabeth were righteous

496
00:23:57,160 --> 00:24:01,700
 "in the sight of God, observing His commands blamelessly,

497
00:24:01,700 --> 00:24:05,040
 "and even after doubting, He was obedient

498
00:24:05,040 --> 00:24:07,940
 "and followed the word of the Lord,

499
00:24:07,940 --> 00:24:12,060
 "praising God and looking to Him as the most important."

500
00:24:12,060 --> 00:24:16,560
 What he had just experienced was an afterthought.

501
00:24:16,560 --> 00:24:19,720
 When he looked ahead at what was to come,

502
00:24:19,720 --> 00:24:23,800
 all of the prophecies of old were about to be seen

503
00:24:23,800 --> 00:24:27,640
 in his day, and his son would prepare the way

